race.comment: MISS FINKMEYER (9) bounced back in a big way last start when breaking her maiden over the 1000m trip here. She rates highly on the back of that effort and that form may have already been franked earlier today. Carries now eight after the claim of Nottle and can repeat the dose. PINGERS (7) got the nose down to score in a photo finish first-up at this track and gets the blinkers on for the first time today. The fact she's been kept fresh is very interesting as she boasts a strong fresh record. No reason why she can't go on with the job now. ROLLING RULER (1) flew home in Saturday company at Ascot last start after being a mile back in the run. This suits  much better and the inside draw can see him close to the speed. Ticks a few boxes on the fresh side and can make his presence felt. MAGNASONIC (3) can be thereabouts on resumption. BRAVE SHOT (10) can improve third-up and back in trip.
